docs.abstract: Every month, subscription streaming services add a new batch of titles to their libraries. Here are our picks for December.
docs.snippet: Every month, subscription streaming services add a new batch of titles to their libraries. Here are our picks for December.
docs.lead_paragraph: Every month, streaming services add movies and TV shows to their libraries. Here are our picks for some of December’s most promising new titles. (Note: Streaming services occasionally change schedules without giving notice. For more recommendations on what to stream, sign up for our twice-weekly Watching newsletter here.)

headline.main: The Best Movies and TV Shows Coming to Amazon, HBO Max, Hulu and More in December

docs.abstract: The former pro football player has pushed himself in acting classes, onstage and in films. His latest drama, “Sylvie’s Love,” also meant returning to an early passion: music.
docs.snippet: The former pro football player has pushed himself in acting classes, onstage and in films. His latest drama, “Sylvie’s Love,” also meant returning to an early passion: music.
docs.lead_paragraph: The lead in a romance may seem like a prize for most actors, but the star of the new drama “Sylvie’s Love” had reservations.

headline.main: For His Second Act, Nnamdi Asomugha Made Preparation His Byword
headline.print_headline: He’s Prepared for His Second Act

docs.abstract: For concerned customers, avoiding one of the world’s largest retailers and web service providers is proving harder than expected.
docs.snippet: For concerned customers, avoiding one of the world’s largest retailers and web service providers is proving harder than expected.
docs.lead_paragraph: Blaze Cromwell, a 24-year-old cashier living in Washington, D.C., doesn’t order from Amazon.com or shop at Whole Foods. He doesn’t watch movies or shows on Prime Video. He doesn’t own a Ring or a Kindle. And he doesn’t use Audible, Twitch or Zappos. He’s about as close as one can get to abstaining from Amazon entirely.

docs.abstract: Bryan Fogel’s examination of the killing of the Saudi dissident Jamal Khashoggi had trouble finding a home among the companies that can be premier platforms for documentary films.
docs.snippet: Bryan Fogel’s examination of the killing of the Saudi dissident Jamal Khashoggi had trouble finding a home among the companies that can be premier platforms for documentary films.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bryan Fogel’s first documentary, “Icarus,” helped uncover the Russian doping scandal that led to the country’s expulsion from the 2018 Winter Olympics. It also won an Oscar for him and for Netflix, which released the film.

headline.main: An Oscar Winner Made a Khashoggi Documentary. Streaming Services Didn’t Want It.
headline.print_headline: Khashoggi As Subject Is Hard Sell

docs.abstract: “She’s disrupting the norms around billionaire philanthropy by moving quickly,” an expert on charities said.
docs.snippet: “She’s disrupting the norms around billionaire philanthropy by moving quickly,” an expert on charities said.
docs.lead_paragraph: In her short career as one of the world’s leading philanthropists, MacKenzie Scott has made a mark through the enormous scale of her giving and also through its speed, donating nearly $6 billion of her fortune this year alone.

headline.main: MacKenzie Scott Announces $4.2 Billion More in Charitable Giving
headline.print_headline: A New Force In Philanthropy Gives Billions

docs.abstract: The deal, valued at $300 million, is the latest in a string of acquisitions as streaming platforms expand beyond music and video.
docs.snippet: The deal, valued at $300 million, is the latest in a string of acquisitions as streaming platforms expand beyond music and video.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon is acquiring Wondery, the company behind podcasts such as “Dirty John,” “Dr. Death” and “The Shrink Next Door,” as the race to grab parts of the audio market continues.

headline.main: Amazon Buys Wondery as Podcasting Race Continues
headline.print_headline: Podcasting Race Continues As Apple Acquires Wondery

docs.abstract: India’s film industry, which relied on theatrical releases, is experimenting with going straight to streaming services such as Amazon, Netflix and Disney’s Hotstar.
docs.snippet: India’s film industry, which relied on theatrical releases, is experimenting with going straight to streaming services such as Amazon, Netflix and Disney’s Hotstar.
docs.lead_paragraph: “Coolie No. 1” has all the hallmarks of a big Bollywood film: colorful costumes, larger-than-life sets, foot-tapping music and a melodramatic story about a man who pretends he has a twin to woo the woman of his dreams.

headline.main: Bollywood, Reeling From the Pandemic, Shifts to Streaming

docs.abstract: Silicon Valley is building a powerful influence industry in Brussels, which has “never seen this kind of money” spent this way.
docs.snippet: Silicon Valley is building a powerful influence industry in Brussels, which has “never seen this kind of money” spent this way.
docs.lead_paragraph: A leaked document jolted the European Union capital of Brussels in October, laying out in painstaking detail plans by Google to undermine new legislation that could severely damage its digital advertising business.

headline.main: Big Tech Turns Its Lobbyists Loose on Europe, Alarming Regulators
headline.print_headline: Big Tech Sets Its Lobbyists Loose on Europe

docs.abstract: The season is adding pressure on retailers, strained by a pandemic surge in e-commerce and limited by shippers, to deliver gifts on time.
docs.snippet: The season is adding pressure on retailers, strained by a pandemic surge in e-commerce and limited by shippers, to deliver gifts on time.
docs.lead_paragraph: E-commerce became a lifeline for consumers and companies during the pandemic. But this holiday season, online shopping will strain the industry as never before: An estimated three billion packages will course through the nation’s shipping infrastructure — about 800 million more than delivered last year.

headline.main: With 3 Billion Packages to Go, Online Shopping Faces Tough Holiday Test
headline.print_headline: Sales Pile Up, But Deliveries Face a Logjam

byline.original: By Michael Corkery and Sapna Maheshwari
